{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":690,"text":"How can I speak in 10 minutes"},{"time":2945,"text":"about the bonds of women\nover three generations,"},{"time":6513,"text":"about how the astonishing\nstrength of those bonds"},{"time":9588,"text":"took hold in the life\nof a four-year-old girl"},{"time":13225,"text":"huddled with her young sister,\nher mother and her grandmother"},{"time":18080,"text":"for five days and nights\nin a small boat in the China Sea"},{"time":21930,"text":"more than 30 years ago."},{"time":24473,"text":"Bonds that took hold\nin the life of that small girl"},{"time":27051,"text":"and never let go --"},{"time":29507,"text":"that small girl now\nliving in San Francisco"},{"time":32129,"text":"and speaking to you today."},{"time":34939,"text":"This is not a finished story."},{"time":37525,"text":"It is a jigsaw puzzle\nstill being put together."},{"time":41117,"text":"Let me tell you about some of the pieces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44956,"text":"Imagine the first piece:\na man burning his life's work."},{"time":49674,"text":"He is a poet, a playwright,"},{"time":52967,"text":"a man whose whole life"},{"time":54273,"text":"had been balanced on the single hope\nof his country's unity and freedom."},{"time":59253,"text":"Imagine him as the communists\nenter Saigon --"},{"time":62565,"text":"confronting the fact\nthat his life had been a complete waste."},{"time":66450,"text":"Words, for so long his friends,\nnow mocked him."},{"time":70251,"text":"He retreated into silence."},{"time":72727,"text":"He died broken by history."},{"time":76442,"text":"He is my grandfather."},{"time":79087,"text":"I never knew him in real life."},{"time":83011,"text":"But our lives are much more\nthan our memories."},{"time":86410,"text":"My grandmother never\nlet me forget his life."},{"time":89665,"text":"My duty was not to allow\nit to have been in vain,"},{"time":92806,"text":"and my lesson was to learn\nthat, yes, history tried to crush us,"},{"time":97310,"text":"but we endured."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100016,"text":"The next piece of the jigsaw\nis of a boat in the early dawn"},{"time":103555,"text":"slipping silently out to sea."},{"time":106831,"text":"My mother, Mai, was 18\nwhen her father died --"},{"time":110322,"text":"already in an arranged marriage,"},{"time":112528,"text":"already with two small girls."},{"time":115521,"text":"For her, life had distilled\nitself into one task:"},{"time":119226,"text":"the escape of her family\nand a new life in Australia."},{"time":123490,"text":"It was inconceivable to her\nthat she would not succeed."},{"time":127674,"text":"So after a four-year saga\nthat defies fiction,"},{"time":130600,"text":"a boat slipped out to sea\ndisguised as a fishing vessel."},{"time":135413,"text":"All the adults knew the risks."},{"time":138358,"text":"The greatest fear\nwas of pirates, rape and death."},{"time":142996,"text":"Like most adults on the boat,"},{"time":144912,"text":"my mother carried\na small bottle of poison."},{"time":148471,"text":"If we were captured,\nfirst my sister and I,"},{"time":151766,"text":"then she and my grandmother would drink."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155467,"text":"My first memories are from the boat --"},{"time":158273,"text":"the steady beat of the engine,"},{"time":160082,"text":"the bow dipping into each wave,"},{"time":162917,"text":"the vast and empty horizon."},{"time":166045,"text":"I don't remember the pirates\nwho came many times,"},{"time":168572,"text":"but were bluffed by the bravado\nof the men on our boat,"},{"time":172634,"text":"or the engine dying\nand failing to start for six hours."},{"time":177249,"text":"But I do remember the lights\non the oil rig off the Malaysian coast"},{"time":181783,"text":"and the young man who collapsed and died,"},{"time":184541,"text":"the journey's end too much for him,"},{"time":188079,"text":"and the first apple I tasted,\ngiven to me by the men on the rig."},{"time":192586,"text":"No apple has ever tasted the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198185,"text":"After three months in a refugee camp,\nwe landed in Melbourne."},{"time":202247,"text":"And the next piece of the jigsaw\nis about four women"},{"time":204791,"text":"across three generations\nshaping a new life together."},{"time":210115,"text":"We settled in Footscray,"},{"time":212162,"text":"a working-class suburb\nwhose demographic is layers of immigrants."},{"time":216511,"text":"Unlike the settled middle-class suburbs,\nwhose existence I was oblivious of,"},{"time":220836,"text":"there was no sense\nof entitlement in Footscray."},{"time":223903,"text":"The smells from shop doors\nwere from the rest of the world."},{"time":227109,"text":"And the snippets of halting English"},{"time":228817,"text":"were exchanged between people\nwho had one thing in common:"},{"time":232484,"text":"They were starting again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235453,"text":"My mother worked on farms,"},{"time":237312,"text":"then on a car assembly line,"},{"time":238974,"text":"working six days, double shifts."},{"time":242134,"text":"Somehow, she found time to study English"},{"time":244266,"text":"and gain IT qualifications."},{"time":247254,"text":"We were poor."},{"time":249364,"text":"All the dollars were allocated"},{"time":251140,"text":"and extra tuition in English\nand mathematics was budgeted for"},{"time":254562,"text":"regardless of what missed out,"},{"time":257609,"text":"which was usually new clothes;"},{"time":260110,"text":"they were always secondhand."},{"time":262341,"text":"Two pairs of stockings for school,"},{"time":264351,"text":"each to hide the holes in the other."},{"time":266974,"text":"A school uniform down to the ankles,\nbecause it had to last for six years."},{"time":272756,"text":"And there were rare\nbut searing chants of \"slit-eye\""},{"time":276741,"text":"and the occasional graffiti:"},{"time":278495,"text":"\"Asian, go home.\""},{"time":280686,"text":"Go home to where?"},{"time":282969,"text":"Something stiffened inside me."},{"time":285400,"text":"There was a gathering of resolve\nand a quiet voice saying,"},{"time":288801,"text":"\"I will bypass you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":291984,"text":"My mother, my sister and I\nslept in the same bed."},{"time":296651,"text":"My mother was exhausted each night,"},{"time":298912,"text":"but we told one another about our day"},{"time":300993,"text":"and listened to the movements\nof my grandmother around the house."},{"time":305155,"text":"My mother suffered from nightmares,\nall about the boat."},{"time":309488,"text":"And my job was to stay awake\nuntil her nightmares came"},{"time":312526,"text":"so I could wake her."},{"time":316041,"text":"She opened a computer store,"},{"time":317877,"text":"then studied to be a beautician\nand opened another business."},{"time":321479,"text":"And the women came with their stories"},{"time":323282,"text":"about men who could not\nmake the transition,"},{"time":325942,"text":"angry and inflexible,"},{"time":327720,"text":"and troubled children\ncaught between two worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331164,"text":"Grants and sponsors were sought."},{"time":333201,"text":"Centers were established."},{"time":335940,"text":"I lived in parallel worlds."},{"time":338080,"text":"In one, I was the classic Asian student,"},{"time":341142,"text":"relentless in the demands\nthat I made on myself."},{"time":344570,"text":"In the other, I was enmeshed\nin lives that were precarious,"},{"time":347689,"text":"tragically scarred by violence,\ndrug abuse and isolation."},{"time":352719,"text":"But so many over the years were helped."},{"time":354781,"text":"And for that work,\nwhen I was a final-year law student,"},{"time":357717,"text":"I was chosen as the Young\nAustralian of the Year."},{"time":360302,"text":"And I was catapulted from\none piece of the jigsaw to another,"},{"time":364254,"text":"and their edges didn't fit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366813,"text":"Tan Le, anonymous Footscray resident,"},{"time":369084,"text":"was now Tan Le,\nrefugee and social activist,"},{"time":372437,"text":"invited to speak in venues\nshe had never heard of"},{"time":375882,"text":"and into homes whose existence\nshe could never have imagined."},{"time":380313,"text":"I didn't know the protocols."},{"time":382405,"text":"I didn't know how to use the cutlery."},{"time":385114,"text":"I didn't know how to talk about wine."},{"time":387504,"text":"I didn't know how to talk about anything."},{"time":391436,"text":"I wanted to retreat\nto the routines and comfort"},{"time":394377,"text":"of life in an unsung suburb --"},{"time":397485,"text":"a grandmother, a mother and two daughters"},{"time":400131,"text":"ending each day as they had\nfor almost 20 years,"},{"time":403844,"text":"telling one another the story of their day"},{"time":406320,"text":"and falling asleep,\nthe three of us still in the same bed."},{"time":412138,"text":"I told my mother I couldn't do it."},{"time":415714,"text":"She reminded me that I was now\nthe same age she had been"},{"time":419186,"text":"when we boarded the boat."},{"time":421548,"text":"\"No\" had never been an option."},{"time":424879,"text":"\"Just do it,\" she said,"},{"time":426230,"text":"\"and don't be what you're not.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":429137,"text":"So I spoke out on youth\nunemployment and education"},{"time":432385,"text":"and the neglect of the marginalized\nand disenfranchised."},{"time":435876,"text":"And the more candidly I spoke,\nthe more I was asked to speak."},{"time":441257,"text":"I met people from all walks of life,"},{"time":443353,"text":"so many of them doing\nthe thing they loved,"},{"time":445927,"text":"living on the frontiers of possibility."},{"time":448574,"text":"And even though I finished my degree,"},{"time":451000,"text":"I realized I could not settle\ninto a career in law."},{"time":454677,"text":"There had to be another piece\nof the jigsaw."},{"time":457946,"text":"And I realized, at the same time,"},{"time":460302,"text":"that it is OK to be an outsider,"},{"time":462974,"text":"a recent arrival,"},{"time":464736,"text":"new on the scene --"},{"time":466625,"text":"and not just OK,"},{"time":468377,"text":"but something to be thankful for,"},{"time":470671,"text":"perhaps a gift from the boat."},{"time":473292,"text":"Because being an insider can so easily\nmean collapsing the horizons,"},{"time":477890,"text":"can so easily mean accepting\nthe presumptions of your province."},{"time":482968,"text":"I have stepped outside\nmy comfort zone enough now"},{"time":485399,"text":"to know that, yes,\nthe world does fall apart,"},{"time":488143,"text":"but not in the way that you fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490553,"text":"Possibilities that would not\nhave been allowed"},{"time":492857,"text":"were outrageously encouraged."},{"time":495036,"text":"There was an energy there,"},{"time":496535,"text":"an implacable optimism,"},{"time":498614,"text":"a strange mixture of humility and daring."},{"time":502306,"text":"So I followed my hunches."},{"time":504077,"text":"I gathered around me\na small team of people"},{"time":506587,"text":"for whom the label \"It can't be done\"\nwas an irresistible challenge."},{"time":511375,"text":"For a year, we were penniless."},{"time":513412,"text":"At the end of each day,\nI made a huge pot of soup"},{"time":515778,"text":"which we all shared."},{"time":517947,"text":"We worked well into each night."},{"time":520328,"text":"Most of our ideas were crazy,"},{"time":522613,"text":"but a few were brilliant,"},{"time":524445,"text":"and we broke through."},{"time":527549,"text":"I made the decision to move\nto the US after only one trip."},{"time":531720,"text":"My hunches again."},{"time":533666,"text":"Three months later, I had relocated,\nand the adventure has continued."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539657,"text":"Before I close, though,\nlet me tell you about my grandmother."},{"time":544018,"text":"She grew up at a time when Confucianism\nwas the social norm"},{"time":547665,"text":"and the local mandarin\nwas the person who mattered."},{"time":550947,"text":"Life hadn't changed for centuries."},{"time":554049,"text":"Her father died soon after she was born."},{"time":557676,"text":"Her mother raised her alone."},{"time":560692,"text":"At 17, she became the second wife\nof a mandarin whose mother beat her."},{"time":566731,"text":"With no support from her husband,"},{"time":568749,"text":"she caused a sensation\nby taking him to court"},{"time":571479,"text":"and prosecuting her own case,"},{"time":573735,"text":"and a far greater sensation when she won."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576486,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":583071,"text":"\"It can't be done\" was shown to be wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588625,"text":"I was taking a shower\nin a hotel room in Sydney"},{"time":591677,"text":"the moment she died,"},{"time":593260,"text":"600 miles away, in Melbourne."},{"time":597103,"text":"I looked through the shower screen\nand saw her standing on the other side."},{"time":601258,"text":"I knew she had come to say goodbye."},{"time":603955,"text":"My mother phoned minutes later."},{"time":607316,"text":"A few days later,"},{"time":608630,"text":"we went to a Buddhist temple in Footscray\nand sat around her casket."},{"time":612976,"text":"We told her stories and assured her\nthat we were still with her."},{"time":617725,"text":"At midnight, the monk came\nand told us he had to close the casket."},{"time":623398,"text":"My mother asked us to feel her hand."},{"time":626554,"text":"She asked the monk,"},{"time":628000,"text":"\"Why is it that her hand is so warm\nand the rest of her is so cold?\""},{"time":633678,"text":"\"Because you have been holding it\nsince this morning,\" he said."},{"time":637679,"text":"\"You have not let it go.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":642242,"text":"If there is a sinew in our family,\nit runs through the women."},{"time":647100,"text":"Given who we were\nand how life had shaped us,"},{"time":650077,"text":"we can now see that the men\nthat might have come into our lives"},{"time":653443,"text":"would have thwarted us."},{"time":655366,"text":"Defeat would have come too easily."},{"time":658590,"text":"Now I would like to have my own children,\nand I wonder about the boat."},{"time":663792,"text":"Who could ever wish it on their own?"},{"time":666937,"text":"Yet I am afraid of privilege,"},{"time":669107,"text":"of ease,"},{"time":670337,"text":"of entitlement."},{"time":672457,"text":"Can I give them a bow in their lives,\ndipping bravely into each wave,"},{"time":677518,"text":"the unperturbed and steady\nbeat of the engine,"},{"time":680889,"text":"the vast horizon that guarantees nothing?"},{"time":685439,"text":"I don't know."},{"time":687232,"text":"But if I could give it"},{"time":688653,"text":"and still see them safely through,"},{"time":690991,"text":"I would."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693325,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":706094,"text":"Trevor Neilson: And also,\nTan's mother is here today,"},{"time":709382,"text":"in the fourth or fifth row."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}